'''Bara Tumba''' is an ancient living area from [[Neolithic]] times located near the village of [[Porodin (Macedonia)|Porodin]], [[Republic of Macedonia|Macedonia]], near [[Bitola]]. Discovered in 1953, several objects and some old Neolithic houses have been found. These objects are kept in the Museum of Bitola.

