| {{ntsh|1}}Doric, architect: [[Libon (architect)|Libon]] of Elis.{{r|BF119}} A refined ''peripteral hexastyle'' temple with 13 columns along each side, in the Classical manner. It had pedimental sculpture of "outstanding magnificence".{{r|Strong61}} The local limestone was covered with stucco, while the sculpture, tiles and gutters were marble{{r|B34}} with bronze [[acroteria]]. From 448&nbsp;BC it housed a colossal [[chryselephantine]] statue of [[Zeus]] 12 metres (40 feet) high by [[Pheidias]].{{r|BF119}}
