| style="text-align: center;" |{{ntsh|559.18}}{{cvt|14.6|x|38.3|m|ft|disp=x|}}<br>{{r|BF1235}}
| {{ntsh|2}}The architect, [[Ictinus]], introduced the use of all three orders within a single building and orientated the building north south instead of east west. While the ends appear a regular ''hexastyle'' temple, it is very long for its width, about 2.3:1 The interior had many unusual features including Ionic capitals of unique design, a central [[Corinthian Order|Corinthian]] column and an asymmetrically placed statue of Apollo, lit by a side door facing the morning sun.{{r|BF1235|BF139}}
