| style="text-align: center;" |{{ntsh|-444}}444&nbsp;BC - 440&nbsp;BC<br>{{r|BF112}}
| style="text-align: center;" |{{ntsh|419.19}}{{cvt|13.47|x|31.12|m|ft|disp=x|}}<br>{{r|PersSouPos}}
| {{ntsh|1}}Doric ''peripteral hexastyle'' building, with attenuated columns (6.12m)  and the perfected Classical proportion of being just slightly longer than twice its width and representing, with the [[Parthenon]] and the Temple of Poseidon at Paestum, the ultimate refinement of the Doric Order. Remnants of its frieze depicting the story of [[Theseus]] and the ''Battle of Lapiths and Centaurs'' survive.{{r|Copp478}}
