| {{ntsh|1 }}One of the earliest Doric temples to have survived substantially intact.{{r|MoFaWo48}} Also known as "the Basilica", it is an unusual building with 9 columns across the front, 18 on each side and a row of columns along the centre of the naos; ''peripteral enneastyle'' in plan.{{r|BF1145}} Its columns have very marked entasis (cigar-shaped) and flattened bulging capitals.{{r|BGA61}}
