| style="text-align: center;" |{{ntsh|725.4 }}19.5m x 37. 2m<br/> (64' x 122')<br>{{r|BF131}}
| {{ntsh|3 }}Ionic temple, architect: [[Pythius of Priene]], of ''peripteral hexastyle'' temple, with ratio approximately 1:2. The columns (height: 11.45)(37&nbsp;ft 6 ins)  rest on plinths. Like many other Ionic temples of Asia Minor, there was no frieze.{{r|BF131}}
