| {{sort|BSart|Sart}}<br>([[Turkey]])
| {{coord|38.47921|28.03128}}
| {{sort|ArtemisSardisCyb|[[Sardis|Temple of<br/> Artemis – Cybele]]}}
| style="text-align: center;" |{{ntsh|-325}}c.<br>325&nbsp;BC<br>{{r|BF128}}
| style="text-align: center;" |{{ntsh|4460.44}}{{cvt|48.78|x|91.44|m|ft|disp=x|}}<br>{{r|SD1}}
| {{ntsh|3 }}One of the largest Ionic temples. It was ''dipteral octastyle'', with its entrance to the west. It was left unfinished, with further construction around 275&nbsp;BC and was completed by the Romans. Little remains standing except the foundations, two intact columns and several stumps.{{r|SD1}}
